    <h3 class="post-title">
	 Sculpture Study
    </h3>
	 
    

         <div class="post-body">

          <p>
      <div style="clear:both;"></div>One day in the spring we went to D. C. look at sculptures.  The following are just a few of the ones we visited.<br /><br />This is actually an extreme close up of an Iris Sculpture near the Federal Triangle metro station.<br /><a href="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/irissculpture.JPG"><img src="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/irissculpture.JPG" width="395"></a><br /> <br />A close up of one of the horses from the sculpture in front of the Capital.<br /><a href="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/horse.JPG"><img src="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/horse.JPG" width="395"></a><br /><br />This is part of the gate to the Capital.<br /><a href="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/capitalpanel.JPG"><img src="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/capitalpanel.JPG" width="395"></a><br /><br />The tulips were in bloom that day.<br /><a href="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/tulips.JPG"><img src="http://vicki.ashtonfam.org/pix/schoolblogpics/tulips.JPG" width="395"></a><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
    </p>

        </div>

